  <static seed="105" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring435.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)r^{2}+13\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)r+42\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+7\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Let<rsq/>s start by noting that <m>(a+b)</m> is common to each term, so 
we may write</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)r^{2}+13\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)r+42\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)} = {\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+13r+42\right)}</m></p>
<p>Next we look for factors of <m>42</m> that give <m>13</m> when added; the 
factors that work are <m>7</m> and <m>6</m> so</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)r^{2}+13\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)r+42\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)}={\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+7\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
